# 💻 Experiment 3 – Router Configuration ## 🎯 Objective To demonstrate how to configure IP addresses on a router to enable communication between two PCs through it. --- ## 🧠 Pre-requisites - Understanding of IP Addressing and Subnetting - Classes of IP Addresses - Basic Networking concepts --- ## 🛠️ Components Required | Device | Quantity | |---------|----------| | PCs | 2 | | Router | 1 | | Copper Cross-over Cable | 2 | --- ## 📋 Addressing Table | Device | Interface | IP Address | Subnet Mask | Gateway | |----------|------------------|----------------|------------------|-----------------| | PC0 | Fa0/0 | 192.168.10.2 | 255.255.255.0 | 192.168.10.1 | | PC1 | Fa0/0 | 192.168.11.2 | 255.255.255.0 | 192.168.11.1 | | Router0 | GigabitEthernet0/0 | 192.168.10.1 | 255.255.255.0 | - | | Router0 | GigabitEthernet0/1 | 192.168.11.1 | 255.255.255.0 | -
